One thing to remember is that, at this point, it's about psychology not 
ideology. Everybody who votes based on the real issues has already made up 
their mind. They are tied. All that matters is giving the under 50% who 
typically do not show up a reason to get off their asses and go to the 
polls.

For those who say Hillary won the debate, they are right. The only thing 
she has going for her is that she could be considered more legitimate than 
Donald Trump. To try and use that to her advantage, she's going to attack 
him on whatever she can, large or minute. In the case of this debate, it 
was the minute. If I had to guess, Trump is planning on going on the 
offensive in the final debates, bringing up all the crap she wouldn't want 
you to think about (i.e. emails, the fact she represents a broken system, 
previous comments, and scandals). She has a pickup truck full of crap on 
him and he has a cement truck full of crap on her.

Trump isn't trying to win right now. He's saving that for when the people's 
opinion of him really matters, when it's time to vote.﻿
